cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely categories. The problem also involves databases and retrieving information from them, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) as possible categories. Finally, the paper presents a capacity achieving scheme, which involves coding theory and communication complexity, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible category as well.
